text: I'm a very indecisive person.
Yeah. I am.
I learned this about myself a few years ago
in the oddest place; while watching Lord of the Rings.
Yeah, okay.
I need to set this up.
I was told going into the Lord of the Rings
that the characters are based on mythic images
that are embedded in our collective unconscious.
So, the character you identify with the most
is speaking to who you truly are
at the core of your being
I know.
That's a lot of baggage to take into a matinee, right?
And I found it extra disturbing
when I started to connect with that Gollum guy,
the Smeagol, the...
Yeah
That bald guy who crawls around
arguing with himself all the time.
"We wants the precious!
We wants it. Hobbits stole it from us
and we wants it."
"But the Hobbits are our friends."
"No, they're not our friends.
Thieves! Filthy dirty thieves."
"No we destroys the precious in the fires..."
"No, we takes the precious
and we will be the masters."
Alright, so...
I'm watching that and, to be totally honest,
the only thought in my head the whole time is,
"Oh my gosh! I think like that all the time."
Yeah, I'm serious.
I'll be at a Starbucks getting a drink.
"Uh, the Single Short Latte, please?"
"We gets the lemon bread.
We wants the lemon bread. We do.
It looks so precious!"
"Don't get it. It will make us fat."
"Shut up! I'll go jogging in the morning.
I'll run off the tricksy little sweet bread I.."
"No you won't! You'll sleep in.
You stay you'll run. You asleep right in.."
"Shut up! I deserves-es it!
I deserves-es it!"
